condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Institutional Arrangements | Description :Borrower to cause the Project Implementing Entity (PIE) to carry outthe Project through the Project Implementing Unit (PIU) and Environmental and Social Screening Unit (ESSU) and in accordance withthe Project Agreement, Operations Manual (OM), Environmental andSocial Management Framework (ESMF) and not to amend the same, andto maintain the PIU and ESSU | Frequency :Monthly
Finance Agreement :Mid-term Review | Description :Carrying out of mid-term review and preparation of reports before and after suchreview | Due Date :31-Mar-2015
Finance Agreement :PCG Account | Description :Maintenance of the PCG Account and ensuring that loan proceeds are made in and out ofsaid account | Frequency :Monthly
Finance Agreement :PCG Account | Description :Reaching agreement on the use of loan proceeds prior to the closing date for fundsremaining in the PCG Account at closing

Finance Agreement :PCG Issuance | Description :Selection of Eligible Financial Institutions (EFIs), MSMEs, Sub-loans, andSub-projects, and issuance of Partial Credit Guarantees (PCGs) in accordance with the ESMF, OM, Loan Agreement and ProjectAgreement | Frequency :Monthly
Finance Agreement :Safeguards | Description :Borrower and PIE to comply with ESMF and exclusions listed therein | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Subsidiary Agreement | Description :Borrower to make loan proceeds available to PIE under Subsidiary Agreementunder terms and conditions acceptable to the World Bank | Due Date :15-Apr-2013
